#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Cronl-ontology.md:11
msgid "Purpose"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Cronl-ontology.md:13
msgid ""
"The RONL Ontology defines a vocabulary for organisational governance of "
"Dutch government rules and decision models. It provides properties for "
"tracking validation, certification, and vendor relationships — enabling "
"transparent, auditable governance of government decision logic."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Creference%5Cronl-ontology.md:15
msgid ""
"The ontology defines **properties** only. It reuses existing classes from "
"CPSV-AP (`cpsv:PublicService`, `cv:PublicOrganisation`), CPRMV "
"(`cprmv:DecisionModel`), and W3C ORG (`org:Organization`)."
msgstr ""

